            <p>Search engines display direct answers in several formats:</p>
            <ul class="content-list">
                <li><strong>Paragraph Snippets:</strong> Brief text answers to definitional or explanatory queries</li>
                <li><strong>List Snippets:</strong> Numbered or bulleted lists for process or collection queries</li>
                <li><strong>Table Snippets:</strong> Data in table format for comparison or specification queries</li>
                <li><strong>AI Overviews:</strong> Synthesised answers drawing from multiple sources</li>
                <li><strong>Knowledge Panels:</strong> Entity information displayed prominently for brand or topic searches</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Different content types and query patterns suit different snippet formats. I assess which formats align with your target queries and structure content accordingly.</p>
